<TEXT>
independence a year ago only a few 
former political prisoners dared whisper the word in the nations 
three baltic republics 
today it is the goal of a mass movement putting the three tiny 
lands in direct conflict with the kremlin 
on wednesday a 370mile chain of determined baltic families 
stood hand in hand protesting the soviet annexation of their 
independent nations but that was just the most dramatic 
manifestation of a profound change that has occurred in recent 
months on the soviet unions western frontier 
the activist groups of estonia latvia and lithuania known as 
the peoples front once worked for more authority within the soviet 
union now they are openly calling for restoration of their free 
nations 
the declarations of the peoples front in the past year have 
become ever closer to the ideals our people have carried in their 
hearts for all these 50 years estonian peoples front leader and 
lawmaker marju lauristin said 
all of us would like to have freedom and freedom without 
independence isnt realistic she said 
from the kremlins point of view it is baltic independence 
thats unrealistic and a sharply worded statement from the 
communist party central committee on saturday made that point clear 
things have gone far serious danger is threatening the baltic 
peoples the policymaking body said people should know what 
abyss their nationalist leaders are pushing them toward 
if they managed to attain their goals the consequences could 
be catastrophic for their people their very ability to survive 
could come under question it said the statement was carried on 
national television 
not long ago such a warning from the central committee would 
have sent shudders through many activists on sunday it did little 
more than raise eyebrows in the baltics yet another indication of 
how far the region has come in establishing for itself an identity 
outside the soviet union 
we expected this said raimona sakalouskis a spokeswoman for 
the lithuanian activist group but leaders of the peoples front 
movements didnt interrupt their weekend plans to discuss the 
statement 
